      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Switching from sertraline to St. John's wort without consulting a healthcare professional is not advisable, as it can lead to dangerous interactions and potentially worsen your condition. St. John's wort can actually reduce the effectiveness of sertraline and may increase the risk of serotonin syndrome. It's essential to talk to your doctor before making any changes to your medication. They can provide safer alternatives or adjust your treatment plan to better suit your needs.",
