      "content": "i hear you about the risks but i feel like i know my body better than a doctor who only sees me for 15 mins once a year. if i'm really careful and just take a very low dose of the zoloft for a week or two while starting a standard dose of the st johns wort, isn't that basically just crossing the bridge safely? i've seen people on reddit say it works fine if you don't do both at the same high dose. can you at least tell me what a typical dose for the supplement would be so i know what to look for?",
